%U A182531 420,441,462,484,506,529,552,576,600,625,650,676,702,729,756,784,812
%N A182531 Extremal graph numbers for a triangle with an edge off it.
%C A182531 The largest possible number of edges in a graph on n nodes that does not contain a triangle with an edge off it as a subgraph.
%C A182531 Assuming Colin Barker's conjectures this is A002378 and the positive terms of A000290 interleaved, except for a(3) = 3. - _Omar E. Pol_, Jan 25 2018
%C A182531 From _Falk Hüffner_, Jun 19 2026: (Start)
%C A182531 Colin Barker's conjectures are essentially that for n >= 4, a(n) = floor(n^2/4) = A002620(n). This is true:
%C A182531 The forbidden (not necessarily induced) subgraph is the paw. Clearly every connected component in a paw-free graph is either triangle-free or a K3. Consider a paw-free graph with n >= 4 that has the maximum number of edges. It cannot have more than one K3, since otherwise we could replace two of them by a K3,3 with more edges. If it has one K3, we can get a paw-free graph with the same number of edges by deleting the K3 and attaching three degree-1 vertices to some vertex in a triangle-free component. Thus, for n >= 4 the maximum number of edges in a paw-free graph is the same as the maximum number of edges in a triangle-free graph, which is floor(n^2/4) by Mantel's theorem. (End)
%D A182531 W. Mantel, Problem 28 (Solution by H. Gouwentak, W. Mantel, J. Teixeira de Mattes, F. Schuh and W. A. Wythoff), Wiskundige Opgaven, 10 (1907), 60-61.
%H A182531 Paul Tabatabai, <a href="/A182531/a182531_1.py.txt">Python script (Gurobi), updated version on Jul 28 2020</a>
%F A182531 Conjectures from _Colin Barker_, Jul 04 2016: (Start)
%F A182531 a(n) = (-1+(-1)^n+2*n^2)/8 for n>3.
%F A182531 a(n) = n^2/4 for n>3 and even.
%F A182531 a(n) = (n^2-1)/4 for n>3 and odd.
%F A182531 a(n) = 2*a(n-1)-2*a(n-3)+a(n-4) for n>7.
%F A182531 G.f.: x^2*(1+x-x^2)*(1-x^2+x^3) / ((1-x)^3*(1+x)). (End)
%F A182531 a(n) = A002620(n) for n >= 4. - _Falk Hüffner_, Jun 19 2026
%e A182531 For n=4 the 4-cycle is a graph on 4 nodes that avoids the triangle with an edge off it.
%e A182531 For n>=4, K_{floor(n/2),ceil(n/2)} achieves the maximum number of edges.
%Y A182531 Analogs for other forbidden subgraphs: A002620 (K3), A000212 (K4), A033436 (K5), A033437 (K6), A033438 (K7), A006855 (C4), A006856 (C3&C4).
%K A182531 nonn
